It hits different when you get to care for your parents as the smallest of gestures for the incredible life they’ve given you. 

Love you, Ma. You’re a warrior, and I can’t wait for you to be tearing up the dance floor in a few months when your new knee is fully up and running! First week post-op complete!

Grateful to our family and friends for showing up, for food, and for all of the love to help Ma heal!

What a year! A rollercoaster, riding the highs and lows, and so much momentum built along the way. Thank you to the incredible humans who were with me every step of the way. Here’s to a powerful year ahead. A year of celebration, fun, leaning into community, building towards our dreams and goals, and continuing to maximize our potential!

Thank you all for being here for the ride! Here’s to a year of achieving your dreams and more ahead!!! 🥳✨💕🔥🙌🏽

My best friend turned 35 today! This is the 14th birthday of his we’ve been lucky enough to celebrate together, and it was truly such a beautiful one. This last few years Mitch had a very specific dream: to bring together all his people so worlds could collide and his love of each of them could be shared!

Today, beside the grills, the pool that isn’t quite ready to be opened, and next to the sprinklers and toys we picked up at Walmart yesterday to keep the kiddos happy, so many of our people hung out for the first time in years. They shared their love of Mitch and his impact on their lives, and we all just got to soak in the sun ☀️, and enjoy a perfect Sunday celebrating one of our favourite humans.

Mitch, you are literally sunshine. Your love of the world and others is so pure and so needed!! You help us all make the mundane magical, and value ourselves more than we ever could alone.

I love you. And I’m so excited to keep loving you for decades to come. Happy birthday my love!!

Last night @elizabeth_gilbert_writer gave a masterclass in boundaries and self-compassion. She asked: what would it look like to care for ourselves so well, and protect our peace so well that we face the rollercoaster of life from a state of ease and relaxation. What if we genuinely chose to create a life that centres our health and enables us to pursue exactly what we want and are here to do?

These were precisely the questions I needed to hear! What are you willing to give up to have the life you keep pretending you want? For me, it’s giving up the lie that others are more important to care for than myself. Can’t wait to hear what you share below.

📸 @imaortegaphotography 

#elizabethgilbert #bigmagic #eatpraylove #boundariesarehealthy #prioritiesfirst #protectyourpeace

What an incredible week at @4gamechangers! The depth and breadth of topics and conversations were immense, from the latest tech innovations, to improving well-being and resiliency, insights from those at the forefront of protecting and advocating for human rights globally, and a deeply womanist agenda (with 70% of the speakers on stage being women, something you rarely see!), this was an unforgettable week.

I feel so grateful to have shared the stage with such powerful innovators and change makers. Thank you Hannah, and the full @4gamechangers team for an unforgettable week in Vienna.

I grew up with @ctvnews channel on at breakfast, at dinner, and during a lot of moments in between. My parents created an environment where taking in the news, politics, and debates was part of daily life. Being on The Debate tonight was a full circle moment for me. When I studied journalism in university I knew early on I wouldn’t be a traditional journalist — business and advocacy for women’s economic development were actually calling me. So to now be able to contribute to the national discourse as a business owner, a proud child of immigrants, and someone deeply committed to the future of our country is a really impactful experience.

I’ve been on air many times, often for my resiliency education, but to be on at a time when I would have been sitting at the dinner table with my parents having our conversation be fuelled by what we were hearing on air about the politics and news of the day is so freaking cool.

Also cool, having @byrenira from our @karseva.co team see me on air as she was travelling through the airport! So great! And getting to touch base with my j-school buds @marika.owens and @soduch!

Thanks @mikelecouteur and @radiomike519 for a fun hour of conversation and the production team for such a great time!

Keep going after what you’re called to people — it’ll all find you at the right time and in the loveliest ways!

In May 2016, I had my first surgery to remove cancer from my body and that same month, we premiered our documentary, @dreamgirlfilm at the @obamawhitehouse. I was so proud to bring my parents, family, and friends to this space, to celebrate women founders and the work we’d poured ourselves into for years, and this happened to also be my first pain free day since surgery.

What a trip to have these photos pop up today, in a new season of life that has been so wildly abundant and that I’ve been able to be so present for.

2016 was one of hardest and most character building seasons of my life. I was 26, was grappling with a cancer diagnosis and recovery, I tried (succeeding at times and failing at others) to keep being a strong cofounder and movement builder, and was suffering from depression and the weight of trying to do it all and be the same person I was before my diagnosis.

This season of life broke me. It gave me the pieces of who I once was, and offered me the opportunity to put myself together in a new and powerful way.

Looking back at these photos, I am reminded that we are stronger than we realize. We are stronger than we believe ourselves to be especially in the midst of that which is seeming to tear our lives apart. I know I need this reminder in my worst of times, especially when I didn’t think I could keep going, and I hope it supports you too.

I have been so many different women in the last 33 years. That includes the woman I was in this 2016 season: having been a cancer patient and survivor, a start-up cofounder and film producer, it also includes learning to become a woman who can occasionally put the weight of the world down for a few moments at a time.

So for right now, I’m going to look at the photos, put down the weight of that time and celebrate. Celebrate the massive milestones they represent: first time filmmakers premiering a film at the White House, being someone who grappled with and survived cancer at 26, being someone who was being moulded by the fires of life, and who became so much better for it.

Happy 10th birthday @knix!! 

@joannaknix it’s truly so special to witness your genius up close.

Last night when I asked the question of how the next step vision has evolved for Knix, and what’s most calling you forward, you shared your deep focus on institutionalizing the culture and vision you’ve created of inclusion, acceptance, and constant disruption, and having this company outlast all of us. You shared the call to expand to more industries, and change the status quo towards true inclusion. I could already see it all unfolding. How could I not as we stood in the space where a decade of deep focus, inspired action, grit, listening, and so much more was being celebrated for its impact and staying power? 

Thank you, to you, your team, and every person who supported the vision of Knix for changing so many lives, changing culture, and changing how so many of us see ourselves — myself included.

I am so excited to see all that’s ahead unfold! Congrats @knix!!!

What a night!! So much inspiration, celebration, connection, and fun!

@knix + @joannaknix thank you for your impact, and for changing my relationship with my period and underwear. Also, thank you for creating a space to meet so many online friends from the last few years IRL, and meet some wonderful new ones! So many hugs that filled my cup!!

Final also, after meeting Jo’s after party alter ego after the State Dinner, I realized we were kindred spirits. Here’s to 3 am nights, and to dreaming about strategy (thanks for that last pic @jolly_mitch 😂).

Happy birthday KNIX!!

Two years ago, @maitreyiramakrishnan and I were interviewed for Canadian Asian Heritage Month (last slide throwback!), and I recall a question being asked about the power of representation. I remember redirecting the question to Maitreyi as Never Have I Ever had just launched, and was deeply transforming culture and mainstream representation for so many! As Maitreyi does, she answered with such grace and awareness of the impact the show and her character Devi were having for so many.

Devi represents a version of the complicated, messy, and beautiful reality of what it looks like to be a child of immigrants growing up as a third culture kid. I feel so deeply grateful to have been able to witness parts of the last three years of NHIE impact up close.

Thank you @mindykaling and @loulielang for this show, and for giving a South Asian family the spotlight in this way.

Thank you @netflix / @netflixgolden, @teenvogue, and especially @_productofculture_ for bringing us all together for last night’s Never Have I Ever Had An Inspiration Like You event. There was so much joy, connection, power and celebration pouring out of the room. I’ll never forget it!

NHIE season 4 drops tomorrow. It’s bittersweet to say goodbye to the Vishwakumar family, but I am so deeply grateful we’ve had them to show us what is possible for our community and to galvanize endless others to keep shining and showing the world that our stories matter.

What a night to remember!

Final shoutout to @archanamisrajain + @monikasabbas for three years of supporting and curating incredible events for the show and it’s ongoing launches. What a ride!

This ‘forest fire season’ is actually just the climate crisis in action. What does seeing this bring up for you? 

For me? Events like this aren’t going to change unless we galvanize and accelerate tri-sector and global engagement on the climate crisis and reckon with the speed at which our world is changing. I don’t want this to become our new normal, but also recognize it’s easy to feel helpless in that likelihood. We have to keep fighting for the future of our planet.

These videos are a few weeks apart. It’s so hard to comprehend.

#climatecrisis #newyork #wildfire

Today we celebrated Pride at the flag raising on Parliament Hill and its first Pride brunch with Minister @marci.ien, PM @justinpjtrudeau and ministers from across parties (the only party leader not present was of course PP).

This celebration was joyful, and in recognition of the increased attacks on the 2SLGBTQIA+ communities. Harnessing and celebrating joy in the face of so much hostility is a powerful act. I am moved to live in a country where our government so unabashedly supports and seeks to protect basic human rights, and freedoms. It was a truly powerful and moving day.

Congrats to everyone involved and the planning teams for bringing this to life! Dunerci, Chris and team, congratulations!!

Today I learned about the @rainbowrefugeecanada organization, and the government announced funding to them and 8 other organizations today that are supporting grassroots communities in living life truly as they are. Make sure to check them out!

Happy five years married, my love! What a joy it is to look back on the best 10-days of our lives. The love poured into us from our community, and it moved through us into each other.

One of my favourite traditions we’ve created is taking this week off every year for a staycation to work on our home together, to reminisce, and to celebrate our community and love.

Here’s to many more years and milestones to come. You are the my soulmate and it is the biggest blessing to do life together. I love you so much!!

Here are some of my favourite memories from that week. Slide 3 was our last moments together the night before our Anand Karaj in Grande Prairie on June 30th, 2018. Every time I look at it I can feel the same excitement course through me!

And yes, we did get married on July 1st so we’d have fireworks to celebrate every anniversary! ☀️

Love you @jolly_mitch!!

Photographers! @joelandjustyna @kenyajade @nimboophoto 

I also still can’t believe that Tim Baker from Hey Rosetta! sang our first dance song and me down the aisle in Ottawa, unforgettable!

About Time is one of our favourite movies, and in it the main character collects moments he would come back to. Moments he could relive over and over again.

Sometimes @jolly_mitch and I turn to each other when we are so immersed in an experience and one of us says, ‘This is a moment I’d come back to.’ We usually smile and nod in agreement.

Tonight was truly one of those nights. A moment we would come back to when we were young, singing an entire set of @mumfordandsons songs by heart, and so deeply in love.

Thank you @mumfordandsons, @marcusmumford for an unforgettable show, and for playing our favourite song!

Congrats @heatherkpage88, Kevin, and everyone involved with the @revandrun5000 (here’s looking at you @weathertechcanada)! 

Can’t wait to race again next year, run more than walk the next one, and have Mitch participate in @parkprovince’s best costume on the track contest vs just taking his top off at the finish line.

Funds were raised for the @parkdalefoodbank and we loved learning more about their impact.

On another note, it’s been a summer of health and self care and it feels so good to be getting so active again! Let’s go!!

Komal the explorer ☀️

Quick stopover in Athens before I see my bestie in Sicily! So many beautiful things have already happened in my short few hours here. From the kindness of strangers taking these pictures and sharing some of our stories with one another, to someone showing me how to do some Greek dancing in the street and others joining us right after I took the last video in this carousel.

I love humans. And yes I was anxious prior to coming because life is life-ing and taking breaks and doing solo travel can feel hard, but sometimes the only way through is through, you know?

☀️

That time I got my spark back 🍋 Thank you Italy and my bestie for such a wonderful vacation! Love you @juliekuras!

Anyone else feel the tidal wave of life the last while just taking you for a ride and spitting you back out to figure out who you are and how to reconcile life while still caring enough to move forward?

Just me? 😂 I am really proud of myself for feeling it all, facing it all, and acting from integrity. I’ve truly learned what it means to prioritize filling my own cup, so I can show up and help others. I’ve also learned how to enjoy the sh*t out of life. Because, we deserve to. It’s hard, and why not be able to laugh and feel the pain of it simultaneously?

So here is a roundup of Italy — a highlight of the rollercoaster that has been life this last year, because I don’t quite know how (or if I ever want to) post when it’s the worst.

I realize the point of photo dumps is to have short captions, but I don’t care ☀️

Also, meet my new favourite accessory, V! 📸: Fujifilm x100v

The upside of work from home is I still get to do a national news program from my home office!

Thanks for having me again @mikelecouteur and the team at The Debate! That was an inopportune blink Mike!

Earlier this week I also got to participate in a round table with Minister of economic development and small business @vicfedeli, to share key recommendations that small and micro business owners would be better supported by. It was disheartening to realize many of the 85,000 small businesses that registered in Ontario last year are likely too small for the government to prioritize the needs of, but this is why we keep sharing our stories for support and to be heard.

Thank you @startupcanada x @amazonca for bringing us together!

If you have any questions about improving your thought leadership and improving your industry for the better, check out my free thought leadership training at my link in bio!

Also, I am loving documenting life with my 📸 @fujifilmx_ca x100v, it’s helping life feel creative again!

Keep your friends so close! Cherish them, witness their lives, and invite them to do the same. Let them hold you when you need, and carry them when they need. They are lifelines. They are love personified. Love you my wonderful people both in this carousel and not ☀️ 

Grateful to the humans who held me this summer in joy, pain, love, and so much fun. Some of these folks I am on the cusp of knowing longer than I haven’t (16 years this month!) and that is such a powerful blessing 🌻

“The ultimate touchstone of friendship is not improvement, neither of the other nor of the self: the ultimate touchstone is witness, the privilege of having been seen by someone and the equal privilege of being granted the sight of the essence of another, to have walked with them and to have believed in them, and sometimes just to have accompanied them for however brief a span, on a journey impossible to accomplish alone.”

- David Whyte

Call one of your people, or send a message to your group chat! Let your people know you love them 🫰🏽

Life lately 🌻

Homemade apple cider with maple syrup from our property, the best time with friends, random finds on country roads, the cutest baby, making music with the love of my life, and feeling like myself again.

Cherish what you have, and watch it blossom!
September in a nutshell 🥜

Keynoting and interviewing are two of my superpowers. I first started speaking in front of crowds when I was in elementary school. Ma always encouraged me and pushed me out of my fear and comfort zone to be on stages, and often to speak on behalf of her and Papa at events they would host.

A family friend reminded me that one of the first times she met me I was 11 or 12, and Papa asked me to introduce a politician who was visiting our house for a backyard BBQ fundraiser and I took the patio ‘stage,’ and she said it stayed with her because of how confidently and eloquently I was able to speak at that age.

I was able to use my voice and this skill at a young age to help amplify the impact of my immigrant parents, and that skill now helps me advance the stories, impact, and causes that require our collective attention in the rooms I’m invited to.

I feel so grateful that speaking about systems change, protecting our well-being, amplifying our resilience, and galvanizing collective social transformation is my work now. I am so grateful I get to do what I’m most called to each and everyday using the skills I love most.

Fear of public speaking is said to impact upwards of 70% of the population. When overcome and harnessed, your ability to speak to crowds can elevate your impact and confidence in major ways! Let’s hang out, and help you do more of that. Check out my free thought leadership training (you know where), as a first step to getting there!

Have any questions about public speaking or interviewing? Drop them below!

Also, shout out to my incredible friends who always support me as I rumble with topics and seek to learn more — @prasran and @heatherkpage88 love you so much! Also to @drsarahsaska, @averyfrancis, and @gwadawac for speaking my name in rooms I’m not in!

Thanks to Swift and @sibos (and the sponsors @publicisgroupe @visaca @amazonwebservices) and @elevatetechca for having me! 

Also, I’d love to speak on your stage — reach out to work together!

📸: Fujifilm x100v

So much of my healing has been showing my inner child and younger me the quality of the life we’ve created and how her dreams mattered, helped us find safety and love, and have led to making meaningful impact.

As we get older, going after our goals and dreams can feel harder and more futile at times. This is your reminder that the only person who can throw in the towel is YOU. If it’s time to give up, cool. But if it’s actually time to recentre, recalibrate, and find new ways to go after it, then let’s f*cking go!

Pivot, do what you need to, and keep going!

Halloween in suburbia 🎃. A+!

It’s a tradition on our birthday’s that Mitch and I make sure there’s a candle to blow out just when the clock strikes midnight. This time, I got to be held by my mom, who we’ve been caretaking for the last many weeks post knee replacement, and he showed me the most beautiful gift I could have ever imagined — a collection of videos from so many I cherish most sending me love on my birthday.

When I was younger, someone asked me online what it means to truly love yourself. I didn’t quite know how to answer then, today, it means allowing love to pour into you, keeping promises to myself, holding deep empathy and care for all the parts of myself that sought it out from others, it is reparenting myself.

This last trip around the sun started as one of the hardest of my life, and it transformed into the greatest opportunity and invitation to love myself and those around me so well.

Here’s to honouring our growth, cherishing milestones because we can, and being drenched in love by those who have chosen to deeply witness our lives, and us theirs.

Happy birthday Koko 🥰

I’ve dreamt of this for so many years. Tonight tens of thousands of people released their dreams into the ether, and it took my breath away. I journaled on my lantern before releasing it, and one of my notes was to have our collective dreams brought to life. So use this moment that you’re seeing this video as a moment to dream of what’s possible for you, your community, the things you care for in the world, and let those dreams take root.

Just as I released this, a man proposed to his future wife right beside me… what a dream.

The Yee Peng lantern festival in Chiang Mai, Thailand. It’s held during each full moon in November to commemorate the days lengthening (from monsoon season to cool season) and light entering our lives! As the monks chanted before we released the lanterns, it was a full moment of presence I will never forget. 🇹🇭

This first crop is brought to you by my geriatric travel shoes! Welcome back to my travel photography era!

Travel is a source of such deep inspiration and joy, and so much of it has to do with the people I get to meet and witness. I have been taking photos as a passion, hobby, and for a time a career for 15 years now, and so much of my love of it comes from being able to observe the quirkiness and cuteness of humanity. We all seek to be seen and loved, and in the moments we don’t realize others are watching, we can at times be most ourselves. That’s what I like to capture. The mundane, the essence of others, the beauty of the smallest of moments. Often asking with a simple head nod if I can capture them, and a small smile back, one shutter clicks and we both reenter or unique and full lives.

This was my time at Wat Umong (the temple of tunnels) and Wat Phra That Doi Suthep (the temple on the mountain) in Chiang Mai.

Come cook with me in the Lanna countryside! Meet Lyn. She is the owner of Love Chiang Mai Cooking School and invited us into her countryside home to cook her ancestral foods.

She walked us through the local markets as we picked up the fresh ingredients for our 8-dish meal, and we shared laughs with the vendors who she knows well. Their generosity and curiosity poured through, and so did ours as we peppered Lyn with questions about the local fruits, spices, and meats. This was such a special part of the day.

We drove to her home just outside of Chiang Mai, a place she started renting from a friend many years ago and that she’s turned into an incredible haven and immersive Lanna and Thai cooking den. Year by year she’s built this facility as a single mom. She shared her big dreams for all to come as she saves and prepares to purchase her own property to include overnight stays, more farming, and so much more.

It’s special to witness a stranger’s dreams in action, and to learn their cultural history first hand through food. The north of Thailand was once its own kingdom — Lan Na. The culture remains distinct, though the language has been slowly removed from schools. She shared that although many locals still speak Lanna, you can only see it written and taught in very few temples in the region. I appreciated her nuanced and in depth sharing of her cultural history and it made the meal even more meaningful as we learned the subtle but important differences between Thai and Lanna foods.

At one point I called Ma on FaceTime and she was so excited to see me cooking in clay pots like she had growing up. She hung out with us as I prepared the Green Mango salad — that was a beautiful highlight of the day for me.

@airbnb experiences have truly given me so many local and impactful experiences I wouldn’t have otherwise had, and @lynlovechiangmai is building her own corner of the internet to have more of the world experience her culture and hospitality. If you are looking for an unforgettable trip and day, visit Chiang Mai and send Lyn a message, you won’t regret it!

It’s been a beautiful season of adventure. I realized that I felt like I had lost years of my life, first to cancer, sickness, and recovery in my 20s, then like most of us to the pandemic, and healing past trauma. This last year I wanted to LIVE. And I truly have. With the love of my life by my side, and a powerful community surrounding me. I’ll never forget the year I squeezed every ounce of possibility out of life… not focused on career, but on myself, my healing, my joy, and my people.

10/10 highly recommend you chase your version of this if you’re called to explore what that is. ☀️
